<center>VPS memory limit</center>
<hr>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
	Memory Limit is the maximum total memory usage for processes running and libraries loaded on a VPS server.<br>
<br>
 <i>Memory Limit</i> depends on tasks running on a VPS server.<br>
 <i>Memory Limit</i> cannot be exceeded. No more memory will be allocated if VPS total memory usage reaches <i>Memory Limit</i>.
VPS server total memory usage = resident/virtual memory usage + system SWAP<br>
<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
	<i>* Minimal VPS installation requires ~15-20Mb allocated memory.</i>